oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Willam Walker
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: William Walker (1824-1860) portrait with captions about William Walker and his birthplace and image of the brick house where he was born.
Nashville-born President of Nicaragua, executed by the Honduran government at Truxillo, Honduras, September 12, 1860. Known as the ""Grey-eyed Man of Destiny.""
